SIMPLE: overman
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Overman
<hw>O"ver*man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>-men</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One in authority
over others; a chief; usually, an overseer or boss.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An arbiter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>In the philosophy of <persfn>Nietzsche</persfn>, a
man of superior physique and powers capable of dominating others; one
fitted to survive in an egoistic struggle for the mastery.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overmanner</ent>⟦br⟧
